{
  "schema_version": 1,
  "description": "50 common coding languages. Each entry describes how to extract its publicly-available functions (stdlib + core builtins) into structured training records for Adam-1 distillation. Extraction methods: 'introspect' = use the language's own runtime introspection (Python inspect, Node require+Object.keys, Ruby methods, etc.); 'doc-json' = parse a JSON dump from the language's official doc tool (cargo doc, godoc -json, javadoc); 'parse-headers' = parse C/C++/ObjC headers via clang; 'parse-stubs' = parse type-stub files (.d.ts, .pyi); 'curated' = manually-curated list (no auto-extraction available, ship a static JSON of common functions). Toolchain column = what must be installed locally to run the extractor; if absent, the language's records have to come from a curated/external dump.",
